## Description
Implement wireTestDependencies() function that creates Beads dependencies making each test child issue depend on ALL subtask children of the same epic, with no wiring if an epic has no subtasks, and update wireAllDependencies return type to include testDeps count.

## Implementation Details
Modify src/sync/dependency-wirer.ts to add test dependency wiring capabilities:

1. Add wireTestDependencies function after wireSubtaskDependencies (around line 51):
```typescript
export async function wireTestDependencies(
  tasks: TaskMasterTask[],
  cli: BeadsCli,
  mapper: IdMapper,
): Promise<number> {
  let count = 0;
  for (const task of tasks) {
    // Skip if task has no subtasks - nothing to test
    if (!task.subtasks || task.subtasks.length === 0) continue;

    // Get test issue ID from mapper
    const testIssueId = mapper.getTestIssueId(task.id);
    if (!testIssueId) continue; // No test issue created for this task

    // Get epic ID for this task
    const epicId = mapper.getEpicId(task.id);
    if (!epicId) throw new Error(`Epic ID not found for task ${task.id}`);

    // Wire test to depend on ALL subtasks
    for (const subtask of task.subtasks) {
      const subtaskBeadsId = mapper.getSubtaskId(task.id, subtask.id);
      if (!subtaskBeadsId) {
        throw new Error(`Subtask ID not found for ${task.id}.${subtask.id}`);
      }
      // Test issue (blocked) depends on subtask (blocking)
      await cli.addDependency(testIssueId, subtaskBeadsId);
      count++;
    }
  }
  return count;
}
```

2. Update wireAllDependencies return type and implementation (lines 53-61):
```typescript
export async function wireAllDependencies(
  tasks: TaskMasterTask[],
  cli: BeadsCli,
  mapper: IdMapper,
): Promise<{ epicDeps: number; subtaskDeps: number; testDeps: number }> {
  const epicDeps = await wireEpicDependencies(tasks, cli, mapper);
  const subtaskDeps = await wireSubtaskDependencies(tasks, cli, mapper);
  const testDeps = await wireTestDependencies(tasks, cli, mapper);
  return { epicDeps, subtaskDeps, testDeps };
}
```

3. Update imports if needed - no changes required as all necessary types are already imported.

**Implementation notes:**
- Function follows same pattern as wireEpicDependencies and wireSubtaskDependencies for consistency
- Uses mapper.getTestIssueId(task.id) which was added in task 11
- Only wires dependencies if test issue exists (some tasks may not have test issues)
- Skips tasks with no subtasks entirely (per requirement)
- Each test issue becomes blocked by ALL subtask issues of the same parent epic
- Returns count for stats reporting in main CLI

